This edition of Horace is substantially the same with Mr. Macleane’s abi-idg- ment of his larger edition in the Bibliotheca Classica. The text is unaltered. Only such changes have been made in the notes as seemed necessary to adapt the book to the class room. Discussions respecting the various readings and disputed points have been omitted3 the arguments of the Odes have been introduced from the largcr work3 and Dr. Beck’s Introduction to the Metres has been appended to the notes.
